msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 9"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:0.5"
msgid "9. Duṭṭhullārocanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on telling about what is serious"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.31, pts-cs-bu-pc9.1, pts-vp-en.2.219, ms2V_295
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto chabbaggiyehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍanakato hoti."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan was quarreling with the monks from the group of six."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.3"
msgid "So sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṃghaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ yāci."
msgstr "At this time Upananda committed an offense of intentional emission of semen. He then asked the Order for probation for that offense,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.4"
msgid "Tassa saṃgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi."
msgstr "which he received."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṃghabhattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Just then an association in Sāvatthī was offering a meal to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.6"
msgid "So parivasanto bhattagge āsanapariyante nisīdi."
msgstr "Because Upananda was on probation, he was seated on the last seat in the dining hall."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.7"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū te upāsake etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks from the group of six then told those lay followers,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.8"
msgid "“eso, āvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto tumhākaṃ sambhāvito kulūpako; yeneva hatthena saddhādeyyaṃ bhuñjati teneva hatthena upakkamitvā asuciṃ mocesi."
msgstr "“Sirs, this Venerable Upananda, the esteemed associate of your families, eats the food given in faith with the same hand he uses to emit semen."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.9"
msgid "So sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṃghaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ yāci."
msgstr "After committing an offense of intentional emission of semen, he asked the Order for probation for that offense,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.10"
msgid "Tassa saṃgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi."
msgstr "which he received."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.11"
msgid "So parivasanto āsanapariyante nisinno”ti."
msgstr "And because he’s on probation, he’s seated on the last seat in the dining hall.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_296
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.12"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.13"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.14"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa ārocessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six tell a person who’s not fully ordained about a monk’s serious offense?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.15"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa ārocethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.16"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.220
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.17"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.18"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa ārocessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you tell a person who’s not fully ordained about a monk’s serious offense?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.19"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.20"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: bhikkhusammutiyā → bhik­khu­samma­tiyā (s1-3)
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_297
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:1.21"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa āroceyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk tells a person who is not fully ordained about another monk’s serious offense, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc9.2.1, ms2V_298
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_299
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.5"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr "Another monk’s:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.6"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "a different monk’s."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_300
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.7"
msgid "Duṭṭhullā nāma"
msgstr "A serious offense:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.8"
msgid "āpatti—cattāri ca pārājikāni, terasa ca saṃghādisesā."
msgstr "the four offenses entailing expulsion and the thirteen offenses entailing suspension."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_301
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.9"
msgid "Anupasampanno nāma"
msgstr "A person who is not fully ordained:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.10"
msgid "bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā avaseso anupasampanno nāma."
msgstr "anyone except a fully ordained monk and a fully ordained nun."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_302
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.11"
msgid "Āroceyyāti"
msgstr "Tells:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.12"
msgid "āroceyya itthiyā vā purisassa vā gahaṭṭhassa vā pabbajitassa vā."
msgstr "tells a woman or a man or a lay person or a monastic."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_303
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.13"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "Except if the monks have agreed:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.14"
msgid "ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ."
msgstr "unless he has the permission of the monks."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.14b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 1"

#. HTML: </h3><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.14c"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. HTML: </h4><p>
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_304
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.15"
msgid "Atthi bhikkhusammuti āpattipariyantā, na kulapariyantā."
msgstr "There is permission of the monks with a limit on offenses, but not on families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.16"
msgid "Atthi bhikkhusammuti kulapariyantā, na āpattipariyantā, atthi bhikkhusammuti āpattipariyantā ca kulapariyantā ca, atthi bhikkhusammuti neva āpattipariyantā na kulapariyantā."
msgstr "There is permission of the monks with a limit on families, but not on offenses. There is permission of the monks with a limit both on offenses and on families. There is permission of the monks with a limit neither on offenses nor on families."

#. HTML: </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h4><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_305
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.17"
msgid "Āpattipariyantā nāma"
msgstr "With a limit on offenses:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.18"
msgid "āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti—"
msgstr "offenses are specified:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.19"
msgid "“ettakāhi āpattīhi ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr "“These particular offenses can be informed about.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_306
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.20"
msgid "Kulapariyantā nāma"
msgstr "With limit on families:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.21"
msgid "kulāni pariggahitāni honti—"
msgstr "families are specified:"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.221
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.22"
msgid "“ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr "“These particular families can be informed.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.23"
msgid "Āpattipariyantā ca kulapariyantā ca nāma"
msgstr "With a limit both on offenses and on families:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.24"
msgid "āpattiyo ca pariggahitāyo honti, kulāni ca pariggahitāni honti—"
msgstr "both offenses and families are specified:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.25"
msgid "“ettakāhi āpattīhi ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr "“These particular offenses can be informed about, and these particular families can be informed.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.26"
msgid "Neva āpattipariyantā na kulapariyantā nāma"
msgstr "With a limit neither on offenses nor on families:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.27"
msgid "āpattiyo ca apariggahitāyo honti, kulāni ca apariggahitāni honti—"
msgstr "neither offenses nor families are specified in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.28"
msgid "“ettakāhi āpattīhi ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </span></p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.28a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. HTML: </h4><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_307
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.29"
msgid "Āpattipariyante yā āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti, tā āpattiyo ṭhapetvā aññāhi āpattīhi āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "When there is a limit on offenses, if he tells about other offenses than those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14, pts-vp-pli4.32, ms2V_308
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.30"
msgid "Kulapariyante yāni kulāni pariggahitāni honti, tāni kulāni ṭhapetvā aññesu kulesu āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "When there is a limit on families, if he tells other families than those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_309
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.31"
msgid "Āpattipariyante ca kulapariyante ca yā āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti, tā āpattiyo ṭhapetvā yāni kulāni pariggahitāni honti, tāni kulāni ṭhapetvā aññāhi āpattīhi aññesu kulesu āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "When there is a limit both on offenses and on families, if he tells about other offenses than those that are specified and he tells other families than those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_310
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.1.32"
msgid "Neva āpattipariyante na kulapariyante, anāpatti."
msgstr "When there is a limit neither on offenses nor on families, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 2"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc17, pts-cs-bu-pc9.2.2, ms2V_311
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.1"
msgid "Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the offense is serious, and he perceives it as serious, and he tells a person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_312
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.2"
msgid "Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the offense is serious, but he is unsure if it is, and he tells a person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19, ms2V_313
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.3"
msgid "Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the offense is serious, but he perceives it as not serious, and he tells a person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_314
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.4"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he tells about an offense that is not serious, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21, ms2V_315, pts-vp-en.2.222
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.5"
msgid "Anupasampannassa duṭṭhullaṃ vā aduṭṭhullaṃ vā ajjhācāraṃ āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he tells about the misconduct of a person who is not fully ordained, whether serious or not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22, ms2V_316
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.6"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the offense is not serious, but he perceives it as serious, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23, ms2V_317
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.7"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the offense is not serious, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24, ms2V_318
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.2.8"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the offense is not serious, and he perceives it as not serious, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc25, pts-cs-bu-pc9.2.3, ms2V_319
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.2"
msgid "vatthuṃ āroceti no āpattiṃ,"
msgstr "if he tells about the action which was the basis for the offense, but not the class of offense;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.3"
msgid "āpattiṃ āroceti no vatthuṃ,"
msgstr "if he tells about the class of offense, but not the action that was the basis for the offense;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if the monks have agreed;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.5"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.6"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc26, ms2V_320
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:2.3.7"
msgid "Duṭṭhullārocanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr "The ninth rule, the training rule on telling about what is serious, is finished."
